HABITAT. —
Hyperolius nitidulus
was found on grasses and bushes in floodplains, in swampy valleys and farmland such as maize and paddy fields, plantain plantations and vegetable gardens. It was also found on plants above water at nearby ponds and rivers. This species inhabits shrublands, grasslands and wetlands in the Guinean and Sudanian savannahs, from central Guinea to Cameroon ( Lamotte 1967b ; Rödel 2000 ;
Rödel et al. 2010a
).
